name: Ragnar Trail Richmond - VA
intro: Ragnar Trail Relays and Sports Backers have partnered to bring you Ragnar Trail Richmond-VA (RVA) presented by Salomon.  Only 20 miles from Richmond, Pocahontas State Park boasts some of the finest trail running in Virginia. Ragnar Trail RVA is an overnight trail running relay in which teams of 8 (or 4) run three different loops that start and finish at Ragnar Village. Out on the trails runners will experience views of Beaver Lake, Swift Creek Lake, and billions of stars overhead. Teams will camp overnight in Ragnar Village located on the serene leafy banks of Swift Creek. Ragnar Village will include yoga, bonfires, s’mores, music, sponsor goodies and more. Ragnar Trail RVA will be an unforgettable experience that you won’t want to miss!
home: Ragnar Trail Relays and Sports Backers have partnered to bring you Ragnar Trail Richmond-VA (RVA) presented by Salomon. Ragnar Trail RVA is an overnight trail running relay that kicks off at Pocahontas State Park April 29-30, 2016. Only 20 miles from Richmond, Pocahontas State Park boasts some of the finest trail running in Virginia. Teams of 8 (or 4) run three different loops that start and finish at Ragnar Village. Out on the trails runners will experience views of Beaver Lake, Swift Creek Lake, and billions of stars overhead. Teams will camp overnight in Ragnar Village located on the serene leafy banks of Swift Creek. Ragnar Village will include yoga, bonfires, s’mores, music, sponsor goodies and more. Ragnar Trail RVA will be an unforgettable experience that you won’t want to miss!
village:
Ragnar Village is the heart and soul of the event. Each trail begins and ends in Ragnar Village. It is the start line, the finish line, and the exchange point. After each loop you will return to the support of your teammates and the adulation of the teams around you. Ragnar Village will be complete with:

  • Bonfire
  • S'mores
  • Music
  • Food & snacks (Friday nigh dinner included for each runner*)
  • Partner Tents
  • Billions of stars

*Ragnar strives to provide vegetarian options at all meals. Should you have alternative food preferences (gluten-free, vegan, etc.) or specific dietary requirements, please consider bringing your own food as these options are not always available.

Training by Salomon

At Salomon our goal is to inspire runners to go beyond the pavement and enjoy greater freedom to run anywhere. We believe that with some tips and training almost anyone can become a trail runner and run the Ragnar Trail Relay. We are here to guide you on your training journey as you prepare to run the Ragnar Trail Relay.

charity:
Ragnar Trail Richmond is just around the corner. Make the weekend even more meaningful by fundraising for a Ragnar charity partner or your favorite charity on everydayhero, the official fundraising platform of Ragnar Relay Series! 

Simply go here (or click on the everydayhero logo above) and choose your favorite charity – it’s that easy!  Your fundraising page will be created and you can start making every step count.

In 2016, the Ragnar community fundraised over 2.1 million dollars so let's keep it going for 2017! 

Be A Kids Run RVA Hero

Hit the trails of one of Virginia’s natural jewels, Pocahontas State Park, as a Kids Run RVA hero at the 2017 Ragnar Trail Richmond and experience VIP treatment! With every mile you run, you are helping push forward the programming of Kids Run RVA throughout the greater Richmond region. Learn more and click here...

 

Nathan Chris Baker Foundation
At The Nathan Chris Baker Foundation we believe that greatness lies within each of us. Our goal is to inspire people to Go Out and Be Great, by providing financial, physical and emotional support to individuals, families, and communities in need. Visit us at www.nathanchrisbaker.com.

meta_description: Ragnar Trail Relays and Sports Backers have partnered to bring you Ragnar Trail Richmond-VA (RVA) presented by Salomon.  Only 20 miles from Richmond, Pocahontas State Park boasts some of the finest trail running in Virginia. Ragnar Trail RVA is an overnight trail running relay in which teams of 8 (or 4) run three different loops that start and finish at Ragnar Village.

legs.name: Green Loop - Beaver Lake Trail
legs.description: This Loop leaves the Village along with the Red Loop, and takes you out to the main section of mountain bike trails in the park. After ¾ of a mile, you’ll split right from Red and the single-track adventure begins! The trail has a great flow, leaving you with a fleet feet feel. Around mile 2.5 the trail turns to double-track for a short bit before a quick turn that spits you back onto single-track down to Beaver Lake. For the next mile the trail is pretty constant, offering some great views of the lake. Before you know it, you’ll re-join Red , cross the spillway and climb back up to the Village.

legs.name: Yellow Loop - Swift Creek Trail
legs.description: The Yellow Loop runs parallel to Swift Creek Lake for the first 2.5 miles, crossing mini-bridges, and swooping up and down small contours. Then the trail turns away from the lake and starts the clockwise turn back home. But don’t worry, you’re still in for a few more miles of fun, fast, buffed out single-track before and the loop is done. Just past mile 5 you’ll join up with the Green and Red Loops to kick it back into the Village.

legs.name: Red Loop - Spillway Trail
legs.description: The Red Loop takes advantage of some of the park’s great single-track trails. After splitting away from the Green Loop ¾ of a mile in, things take a turn, and another turn, and another. This trail twists and turns so much you may lose your sense of direction. But don’t worry--just follow the course signage and let the joy flow. Before you know it, you’ll meet back up with the Green Loop on your way back to the Village, smile fully intact.
